<paragraph id="9C135407F2524EF595695E978A518BE8" pageNumber="39">Introduction</paragraph>
<paragraph id="73151D3210C02C6BB9BD02F44DADEAD5" pageNumber="39">
The melanotaenioid family Bedotiidae is endemic to Madagascar and comprises two genera, 
<taxonomicName id="8A58707DBBDDA050D116D7ABA469A35B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="39" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4D639C601887A14B1D2174C9A4C01B78" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3542FCEF-72BD-403C-9EC3-A1A2C08D7452" authorityName="Jordan &amp; Hubbs" authorityYear="1919" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Rheocles" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rheocles Jordan &amp; Hubbs 1919:343" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="39" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rheocles</taxonomicName>
. As their common name, Malagasy rainbows or rainbowfishes, implies, bedotiids generally are colorful fishes. Bedotiids are elongate, laterally compressed, and rarely exceed 100.0 mm SL. Most bedotiids exhibit varying degrees of sexual dimorphism, which is quite pronounced in some species. Bedotiids occur exclusively in freshwater environments and are distributed in small to medium-sized forested rivers and streams, occasionally in swamps and marshes, spanning nearly the entire eastern versant of Madagascar. All species of 
<taxonomicName id="C9A819FFF13862E37120AFEAA2C3A78F" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="39" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8B3F69BDB8EE72DEF48C967E5543AE98" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3542FCEF-72BD-403C-9EC3-A1A2C08D7452" authorityName="Jordan &amp; Hubbs" authorityYear="1919" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Rheocles" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rheocles Jordan &amp; Hubbs 1919:343" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="39" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rheocles</taxonomicName>
are restricted to eastern drainages, less 
<taxonomicName id="5FA66F6950562C850834B827417C7CB2" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:63B9D30B-03C8-4BD7-8D93-E8C211A22443" authorityName="Stiassny &amp; D. M. RodrÃ­guez" authorityYear="1992" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Rheocles" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rheocles derhami Stiassny &amp; Rodriguez 2001:99" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="39" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="derhami">R. derhami</taxonomicName>
, which is endemic to a tributary of the westward draining Sofia River located in the northeast of the island.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87827F18A631C2CAF6E51244A6822521" pageNumber="40">
In a species-level phylogenetic hypothesis for Bedotiidae based on an analysis of nucleotide characters from a combination of mitochondrial and nuclear genes, Sparks and Smith (2004a) demonstrated that Bedotiidae and 
<taxonomicName id="206D8B9C8C0D62545A902D9F617314A6" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia</taxonomicName>
are monophyletic, but that 
<taxonomicName id="CFBA27A358352C6D5EFB3F3883703544" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3542FCEF-72BD-403C-9EC3-A1A2C08D7452" authorityName="Jordan &amp; Hubbs" authorityYear="1919" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Rheocles" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rheocles Jordan &amp; Hubbs 1919:343" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rheocles</taxonomicName>
is paraphyletic (Fig. 1). A comprehensive phylogenetic analysis of 
<taxonomicName id="F7484A7A2DEA0BD54AF25D3E9257C464" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia</taxonomicName>
has yet to be undertaken via the use of anatomical features; nevertheless, monophyly of the genus has been hypothesized in a number of recent comparative morphological studies (Stiassny 1990; Dyer &amp; Chernoff 1996; Aarn &amp; Ivantsoff 1997). Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="FD58097304E0A47BF8F91925AD3E3C5C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the presence of a deep notch, the &quot;Bedotia notch&quot;, on the dentigerous margin of the premaxilla (Stiassny 1990: fig. 16a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="705FB6EEC8FEDF15288C0FDF0DBBF25F" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName id="0FE718082B65D1A2D0D541439EE749CC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authority="Regan 1903" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia Regan 1903</taxonomicName>
comprises six nominal species (
<taxonomicName id="036BA1EBFDB605CBDDF53F8CA3289DE4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:0C76202C-046B-46D4-B608-C0A4A04D9C49" authority="Regan 1903" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia madagascariensis Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">B. madagascariensis Regan 1903</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C83CEFC8309D5E2C01C38800A1C442E3" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B0E2DDCE-FA1C-49BC-B212-652EA52C8420" authority="Pellegrin 1907" authorityName="Pellegrin" authorityYear="1907" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia geayi Pellegrin 1907:205" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geayi">B. geayi Pellegrin 1907</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9F68E26ECEA61B7C811B95C2152E3F7D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CC3FB4B2-2C1F-473B-9573-057FF6892B36" authority="Pellegrin 1914" authorityName="Pellegrin" authorityYear="1914" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia longianalis Pellegrin 1914:178" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longianalis">B. longianalis Pellegrin 1914</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="84A61A878C51C29F26A87FBC93219FC0" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CCF0E501-2D2F-4CB3-A7D7-065CC510E839" authority="Pellegrin 1932" authorityName="Pellegrin" authorityYear="1932" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia tricolor Pellegrin 1932:85" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tricolor">B. tricolor Pellegrin 1932</taxonomicName>
, B. 
<taxonomicName id="F746BE7FC664E499C43732B667778255" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AB6300F7-7D5F-4558-9C71-27538D6DEBD2" authority="Stiassny &amp; Harrison 2000" authorityName="Stiassny &amp; Harrison" authorityYear="2000" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia marojejy Stiassny &amp; Harrison 2000:144" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marojejy">marojejy Stiassny &amp; Harrison 2000</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="1E24BD0507920963EB8B988DDACA4130" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F14921E7-7CD9-46AB-92BD-A8B86467A469" authority="Sparks 2001" authorityName="Sparks" authorityYear="2001" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia masoala Sparks 2001:483" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="masoala">B. masoala Sparks 2001</taxonomicName>
). Apart from coloration, pigmentation pattern, and minor variations in body shape, 
<taxonomicName id="0F9DFD376E513EA7C7BB3D909DD65697" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia</taxonomicName>
is a morphologically conservative group of fishes. Until recently, the genus was poorly represented in museum collections, which has precluded detailed phylogenetic studies of their intrarelationships. Fortunately, much additional material has been collected from throughout eastern Madagascar over the past 15 years (Loiselle &amp; Stiassny 2003; Sparks &amp; Stiassny 2003). An examination of these collections, which comprise several newly discovered populations from remote regions of the island, reveals several presumably new species that are distinguishable in terms of pigmentation pattern, coloration, and body shape (Sparks &amp; Stiassny 2003).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="46922D728C090B604008450012A1DF95" pageNumber="41">
Sparks and Smith (2004a) included all nominal species of 
<taxonomicName id="8D5E21BF9672C95CCD47BDB46C60DCD0" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia</taxonomicName>
in their molecular phylogenetic study of rainbowfishes, as well as representatives from these recently discovered populations (Fig. 1). Within this phylogenetic framework for 
<taxonomicName id="E7E0F2EE0449A5A3AABFA7DEDF2E92C1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia</taxonomicName>
, and based on morphological comparisons to all nominal and undescribed species of the genus, including the type series for all species, a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="45824F4FEE3CC8C24B9A3CFD5876AA53" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia</taxonomicName>
from the southeastern highlands of Madagascar is described. A brief discussion on the biogeography of 
<taxonomicName id="0442AE0ECD2067FC3DCB4AEA7931F2E1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:95830A4E-6B41-4B2D-A097-B8713BC0E8AA" authorityName="Regan" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bedotiidae" genus="Bedotia" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Bedotia Regan 1903:416" order="Atheriniformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Bedotia</taxonomicName>
is also presented.
</paragraph>
